dalserver

Class KeywordFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • dalserver.KeywordFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SiapKeywordFactory, SpectrumKeywordFactory, SsapKeywordFactory, XMLConfiguredKeywordFactory

    public class KeywordFactory
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable
    KeywordFactory implements a factory class for well-known DAL keywords, including Groups, Params and Fields. The use of a factory class frees the client from having to know all the detailed metadata associated with each type of keyword. Keywords are indexed by both their ID and UTYPE tags. In general UTYPE is required to ensure uniqueness, but within a limited scope, the ID tag may be sufficient to uniquely identify a keyword without having to know the full UTYPE.

            java.lang.String utype,
            java.lang.String ucd,
            java.lang.String descr,
            java.lang.String hint)
        Add a new Group keyword to the dictionary.
        Parameters:
        name - The default name for the parameter, or null.
        id - The ID by which the keyword is known locally.
        gid - The Group ID identifying the Group.
        utype - The UTYPE tag (data model field identifier).
        ucd - The UCD tag of the group, if applicable.
        descr - A short string describing the Group.
        hint - Hint codes for a group element.

      • addParam

        public void addParam(java.lang.String name,
            java.lang.String value,
            java.lang.String id,
            java.lang.String gid,
            java.lang.String type,
            java.lang.String size,
            java.lang.String unit,
            java.lang.String utype,
            java.lang.String ucd,
            java.lang.String descr,
            java.lang.String fits,
            java.lang.String csv,
            java.lang.String hint)
        Add a new Param (or Field) keyword to the dictionary.
        Parameters:
        name - The default name for the parameter, or null.
        value - The default value for the parameter, or null.
        id - The ID by which the keyword is known locally.
        gid - The ID of the group to which the keyword belongs.
        type - The VOTable-style datatype of the keyword.
        size - The number of elements, for array-valued keywords.
        unit - The units of the keyword value, as a string.
        utype - The UTYPE tag (data model field identifier).
        ucd - The UCD tag (semantic type of the keyword value).
        descr - A short string describing the keyword.
        fits - The FITS keyword equivalent, if any.
        csv - The CSV mapping and lable, if any.
        hint - Set to "p" if the field defaults to a param.

      • idIterator

        public java.util.Iterator<java.lang.String> idIterator()
        Return an iterator for the keyword ID values. The values can then be used to retrieve the corresponding parameter objects. It is assumed that all parameters have a unique id. This method is guaranteed to return the ids in the order they were added.

      • addFields

        public void addFields(RequestResponse response,
             java.lang.String hint)
               throws DalServerException
        Add the indicated keywords from the current keyword factory to a RequestResponse object. The keywords to be added are flagged using the "hint" parameter.
        Parameters:
        response - Request response object to be modified.
        hint - Only generate code for parameters which match one of the specified hint characters. A null value means output all keywords.
        Throws:
        DalServerException

      • printDoc

        public void printDoc(java.lang.String fname,
            java.lang.String title,
            java.lang.String hint)
        Generate an HTML version of a keyword dictionary. The generated file should be copied to the dalserver/doc-files directory to have it included in the javadoc.
        Parameters:
        fname - The name of the output file to be created.
        title - The title for the HTML page.
        hint - Print only keywords which match the given "hint" value. A null value means print everything.
